5|$|At {{the end of}} the episode, the Doctor travels {{into the}} pocket {{universe}} and receives transmitted images of <b>his</b> <b>companions</b> in the subwave signal. After Davros hijacks the signal and taunts the Doctor about his resurrection and imminent victory, the Doctor breaks communication and attempts to convene with <b>his</b> <b>companions.</b> The Doctor lands on the same street Rose is searching for him on and runs to embrace her, but is shot by a Dalek. Jack promptly destroys the Dalek and helps Rose and Donna carry the Doctor into the TARDIS, where the Doctor begins to regenerate.|$|E
5|$|The Doctor {{suspects}} {{that he has}} managed to set back Dalek evolution by several centuries, and considers his mission complete. He and <b>his</b> <b>companions</b> say goodbye to the surviving Thals and Mutos before using the Time Ring to return to Earth and their own time.|$|E
