5|$|Keltset sacrifices {{himself to}} save <b>his</b> <b>companions</b> during the Skull Kingdom's destruction. In the south, the Northland army retreats after the Warlock Lord's downfall. Allanon saves Shea's life and reveals himself as Bremen's centuries-old son, before disappearing to Sleep. Peace {{returns to the}} Four Lands. Balinor takes up his country's rule, while Dayel and Durin return to the Westland, and Menion returns to Leah with Shirl. Shea and Flick reunite and return to Shady Vale.|$|E
5|$|St. Vrain and {{his party}} were {{attacked}} while en route from Dixon's Ferry, Illinois (now Dixon) to Galena, Illinois. St. Vrain had been ordered by General Henry Atkinson to deliver dispatches to Fort Armstrong. Colonel Henry Dodge's men interred the remains of St. Vrain and <b>his</b> <b>companions</b> after the massacre.|$|E
5|$|The Torah, {{although}} disallowing {{the use of}} most insects as food, {{permits the}} consumption of certain locusts; specifically, the red, the yellow, the spotted grey, and the white are considered permissible. In Islamic jurisprudence, eating locusts is considered halal. The Prophet Muhammad {{was reported to have}} eaten locusts during a military raid with <b>his</b> <b>companions.</b>|$|E
